ch 6, 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"April/Film\">{{cite web |last1=Pearson |first1=Ben |title=Everything Coming to Quibi in April, Including \u201950 States of Fright\u2019, \u2018Dishmantled\u2019, and Much More |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/everything-coming-to-quibi-in-april-2020/ |website=[[/Film]] |date=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{Quibi}}\n{{Lists of TV programs by country}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of television series by streaming service]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n[[File:Quibi Logo.png|120px|frameless|right]]\n\n'''[[Quibi]]''' is an [[Over-the-top media service|over-the-top]] American short-form streaming platform that generates content for viewing on mobile devices. To capitalize on mobile viewing specifically, Quibi provides \"quick bites\" of content that can be viewed under 10 minutes, and the content utilizes \"Turnstyle\" technology in order dynamically switch between portrait and landscape viewing formats.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ramos |first1=Dino-Ray |title=Quibi\u2019s Tom Conrad Addresses Platform Skepticism And Reinvented Storytelling \u2013 CES |url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/quibi-tom-conrad-short-form-streaming-platform-ces-consumer-electronics-show-jeffrey-katzenberg-meg-whitman-1202823763/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=January 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\nQuibi's content falls into three main categories:<ref name=\"/Film-90\">{{cite web |last1=Evangelista |first1=Chris |title=Quibi Offering 90-Day Free Trial For Potential Subscribers |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/quibi-free-trial/ |website=[[/Film]] |date=March 6, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"vineyard-nyt\" />\n*Movies in Chapters: Longer features broken into chapters of 7\u201310 minutes\n*Unscripted and Docs: Shows that are episodic in nature and are 10 minutes or less\n*Daily Essentials: Daily curated quick bites of news, entertainment, and inspiration in the 5\u20136 minute range\n\n==Original programming==\n{{Dynamic list}}\n\n===Drama===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Title\n!Category\n! Genre\n! Premiere\n! Notes\n|-\n| ''50 States of Fright''\n| rowspan=\"4\" |Movies in Chapters\n| [[Horror fiction|Horror]]\n| April 6, 2020 <small>(early access)</small><br />April 13, 2020\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slashfilm.com/50-states-of-fright-trailer-new/ |title=\u201950 States of Fright\u2019 Trailer: Sam Raimi and Quibi Are Ready to Scare You|work=/Film |date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020|first=Chris |last=Evangelista}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Donnelly|first1=Matt|title=Jeffrey Katzenberg's Mobile Content Platform Orders Series From Jason Blum, Guillermo del Toro|url=https://variety.com/2018/biz/news/jeffrey-katzenbergs-wndrco-orders-series-from-jason-blum-guillermo-del-toro-1202975458|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=June 21, 2019|date=October 10, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"April/Film\" />\n|-\n|''Most Dangerous Game''\n|[[Action fiction|Action]] [[Thriller (genre)|thriller]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" |April 6, 2020\n|<ref name=\"vineyard-nyt\" /><ref name=\"/Film-90\" />\n|-\n|''Survive''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Thriller (genre)|Thriller]]\n|<ref name=\"vineyard-nyt\" /><ref name=\"/Film-90\" />\n|-\n|''When the Streetlights Go On''\n|<ref name=\"vineyard-nyt\" /><ref name=\"/Film-90\" />\n|}\n\n===Comedy===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Title\n!Category\n! Genre\n! Premiere\n! Notes\n|-\n| ''[[Flipped (TV series)|Flipped]]''\n|Movies in Chapters\n| [[Comedy]]\n|April 6, 2020\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/will-forte-kaitlin-olson-to-headline-quibi-comedy-series-flipped-eva-longoria-arturo-castro-andy-garcia-also-star-1202702721/|title=Will Forte & Kaitlin Olson To Headline Quibi Comedy Series 'Flipped', Eva Longoria, Arturo Castro & Andy Garcia Also Star|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=August 26, 2019|access-date=2019-09-24}}</ref><ref name=\"/Film-90\" />\n|-\n|''Nikki Fre$h''\n|Unscripted and Docs\n|\n|April 6, 2020\n|<ref name=\"vineya